h other military families-black, white, Hispanic, and Asian-created a local politics of inclusion that continues to serve as a reminder that integration can work to change ideas about race. Though Seaside's relationship with the military makes it unique, at the same time the story of Seaside is part and parcel of the story of 20th century American town life. Its story contributes to the growing history of cities of color-those minority-majority places that are increasingly the face of urban America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aAfrican AmericansxHistoryx20th centuryxCaliforniaxSeaside. 0aAfrican AmericanszCaliforniazSeasidexHistoryy20th century. 0aMilitary townsxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aMilitary townsxSocial aspectsxUnited States. 0aMilitary townsxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aMilitary townszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMinoritiesxHistoryx20th centuryxCaliforniaxSeaside. 0aMinoritieszCaliforniazSeasidexHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477844240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804778442423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804778442.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles